<li id="cite_note-Smith_Meaning_and_End-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Smith_Meaning_and_End_31-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1991" class="citation book">Smith, Wilfred Cantwell (1991). <i>The Meaning and End of Religion</i>. Minneapolis: Fortress Press. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-8006-2475-0" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-8006-2475-0"><bdi>978-0-8006-2475-0</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Meaning+and+End+of+Religion&amp;rft.place=Minneapolis&amp;rft.pub=Fortress+Press&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-8006-2475-0&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Wilfred+Cantwell&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
