<li id="cite_note-39"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFKuroda1996" class="citation journal"><a href="/wiki/Toshio_Kuroda" title="Toshio Kuroda">Kuroda, Toshio</a> (1996). Translated by Jacqueline I. Stone. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20030323095019/http://www.nanzan-u.ac.jp/SHUBUNKEN/publications/jjrs/pdf/477.pdf">"The Imperial Law and the Buddhist Law"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i>Japanese Journal of Religious Studies</i>: 23.3–4. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.nanzan-u.ac.jp/SHUBUNKEN/publications/jjrs/pdf/477.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> on 23 March 2003<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">28 May</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Japanese+Journal+of+Religious+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=The+Imperial+Law+and+the+Buddhist+Law&amp;rft.pages=23.3-4&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.aulast=Kuroda&amp;rft.aufirst=Toshio&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nanzan-u.ac.jp%2FSHUBUNKEN%2Fpublications%2Fjjrs%2Fpdf%2F477.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
